******
[4] India: preventive measures at 24 airports
Date: 19 Nov 2014
Source: Times of India [edited]
http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/A-day-after-man-tests-positive-for-Ebola-in-Delhi-Centre-says-situation-under-control/articleshow/45203302.cms


A day after the 1st Ebola case was reported in India, Health Minister JP Nadda on Wed [19 Nov 2014] said arrangements similar to the ones at Delhi airport that helped detect the virus in a man returning from Liberia have been put in place at 24 airports. Nadda stressed that the situation was under "complete control"... - more

